      <p class="mb-2 text-uppercase small">Laura Moy</p>
      <h1 class="mb-2">The Rehearsal Space</h1>
      <p class="text-muted mb-0">June 2015</p>
    </header>

    <div class="row g-4 align-items-start mb-4">
      <div class="col-12 col-md-4 col-lg-3">
        <figure class="mb-0">
          <img src="/assets/images/laura-moy.jpg" alt="The Rehearsal Space" class="img-fluid w-100">
        </figure>
      </div>

      <div class="col-12 col-md-8 col-lg-9">
        <p>
          when there is too much noise / movement, in the world / my head, I find I have shut my eyes
          to find stillness.
        </p>

        <p>
          silence between two people in a room<br>
          can be so loud.<br>
          ...knowing how to break it
        </p>

        <p>
          power of silence...<br>
          to walk into a big, silent room...<br>
          who dares to break the silence...<br>
          it is big... present... louder than loud
        </p>

        <p>
          in silence... so much to be heard<br>
          in stillness so much to be seen / felt.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="thought-piece">
      <p>Stillness = calm</p>

      <p>When mind stills from its whirring.</p>

      <p>No excess or unnecessary movement.</p>

      <p>What is essential, basic, the bones.</p>

      <p>We are never still.</p>

      <p>But how still can we be...</p>

      <p>
        Internal processes of body... continual... blood rushing through...every system...breathing - whole body.
        Signals transmitted.
      </p>

      <p>Stillness found in observing. In giving focus.</p>

      <p>To not disturb the air.</p>

      <p>
        So many sounds from the body as it moves - my body moving - I hear breath, bones cracking, limbs moving
        through air &amp; across floor...
      </p>

      <p>The longer we listen to silence the more we hear...</p>

      <p>Mornings in silence... best thing</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
